%N A395142 Numbers k such that sigma(k) = psi(k) + tau(k) + Omega(k)^10.
%C A395142 Contains 30205446*p^2 where gcd(p, 30205446) = 1 and p prime so a(5) <= 30205446 * 13^2 = 5104720374 and the sequence is infinite. - _David A. Corneth_, Apr 14 2026
%e A395142 21845375 is a term since sigma(21845375) = 27263184 = 26214600 + 8 + 4^10 = psi(21845375) + tau(21845375) + Omega(21845375)^10.
%o A395142 (PARI) isok(k) = {my(f = factor(k)); sigma(f) == prod(i=1, #f~, (f[i, 1]+1) * f[i, 1]^(f[i, 2]-1)) + numdiv(f) + bigomega(f)^10; } \\ _Amiram Eldar_, Apr 14 2026
